Browning Hi-Power SA Pistol; 1980's Feg, Hungarian Production; 9mm LugerOutstanding Hungarian-made Browning Hi-Power...likely produced in the 1980's, this is a solid example of the finest Hi-Power clone ever manufactured. Originally manufactured to supply Hi-Powers to the Warsaw Pact nations, the Feg Browning Hi-Power was a close enough copy that nearly all parts are interchangable with the Belgian-made original. This model was the first choice for countless European police agencies, and were even substituted for the "genuine" item in a shipment to Sadaam Hussein's government(roll-marked with fraudulent FN addresses). Appearing to have seen some degree of duty carry, this weapon may have been a European police trade-in prior to import. No longer in production, collector's have taken notice, but this weapon would still be an ideal duty or self-defense handgun for anyone looking for a Hi-Power and not wanting to break the buget.
